Dialogue: 5,0:17:05.31,0:17:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We mushi-shi use them as guides when we hold rituals.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:09.03,0:17:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,While there are many mushi that are attracted to sake,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:11.75,0:17:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoujounohige only bring real kouki back to their nests.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:15.23,0:17:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If even {\i1}they{\i0} were deceived,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:17.69,0:17:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,your sake's quite impressive.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:21.43,0:17:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:22.54,0:17:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll believe your story.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:24.47,0:17:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll let me go?{198}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:26.75,0:17:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Under one condition:
Dialogue: 5,0:17:28.25,0:17:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that you do not distribute that sake to others.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:32.19,0:17:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sake that allows people to see mushi would probably cause a lot of unnecessary trouble.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:39.05,0:17:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, even if the taste is exemplary,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:41.18,0:17:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt a sake that makes people "hallucinate" would be good for your brewery's image.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:50.67,0:17:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What you used as "yeast" was likely a Suimitsutou, or "Nectar Sucker" mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:58.21,0:18:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Like yeast, they are microscopic, and they \Nmetabolize sugar, fermenting it until it becomes sake.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:03.53,0:18:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Some have said that Suimitsutou may be used to brew fake kouki,{counterfeit kouki}
Dialogue: 5,0:18:07.51,0:18:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but no known attempts at this have succeeded.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:11.23,0:18:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, your brewing skills are beyond compare.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:17.75,0:18:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,May I ask you something?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:19.28,0:18:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this "kouki" that you keep mentioning?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:24.09,0:18:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the essence of life itself.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:26.91,0:18:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a panacea for those who suffer from mushi-related afflictions.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:30.51,0:18:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And what are "mushi"?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:32.23,0:18:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:33.49,0:18:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they're part of that which shapes this world.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:39.14,0:18:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing more, nothing less.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:44.07,0:18:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, about that sake you brewed...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:46.33,0:18:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:48.27,0:18:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Although you're not able to distribute it {\i1}openly{\i0}...{this is a v. tricky line because, uh, how should i explain this... the 'officially' part also applies to himself. as in, when he said that it shouldn't be distributed, he was talking from an "official" or surface standpoint, if that makes any sense}
Dialogue: 5,0:18:53.41,0:18:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:00.09,0:19:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The following morning,
Dialogue: 5,0:19:02.25,0:19:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I returned to the brewery to find everyone in an uproar
Dialogue: 5,0:19:06.24,0:19:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}because they had gotten drunk and had "hallucinated."
Dialogue: 5,0:19:11.49,0:19:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After a discussion,
Dialogue: 5,0:19:13.06,0:19:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}we decided to not sell or distribute that sake \Nbut to keep it in the storeroom for the time being.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:19.87,0:19:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We kept it because, from time to time, \Nwe'd get strange visitors who wanted to buy it.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:27.11,0:19:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do these people even learn about that sake?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:31.60,0:19:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:37.33,0:19:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by "openly"?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:40.49,0:19:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that sake could be useful to us mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:42.97,0:19:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll send out word that there's a brewery that makes interesting sake.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:47.12,0:19:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But won't that cause them to come after me?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:50.73,0:19:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're only selling it, it shouldn't be a problem.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:54.09,0:19:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They gave you a hard time just now \Nbecause you were trading it as kouki.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:57.71,0:19:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all about how you use it.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:00.37,0:20:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you mushi-shi use it?{the lit./engrish-y tl for it would "what use is there", so i'd say it's more the former}
Dialogue: 5,0:20:02.41,0:20:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in a lot of different ways.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:04.93,0:20:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many cases that can be solved by making the invisible visible.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:13.63,0:20:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:15.11,0:20:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So you met those people just as I did.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:19.47,0:20:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Though that man shared his sake with me, it wasn't nice of me to trade him this.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:24.43,0:20:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, did you decide to try that sake?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:28.45,0:20:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:30.21,0:20:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You should've. It was delicious.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:33.01,0:20:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:35.33,0:20:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the taste of {\i1}your{\i0} sake, Dad.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:39.45,0:20:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I plan to try again from square one to reach that level—properly this time.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:47.87,0:20:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be able to hear what the sake is saying.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:09.17,0:21:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Since that evening, I never saw those mushi-shi in the mountains again.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:13.85,0:21:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The golden sake we made is almost gone, too.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:18.75,0:21:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There are still times when the sake we brew doesn't turn out well.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:23.45,0:21:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At times like those,
Dialogue: 5,0:21:27.87,0:21:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I drink some of that golden sake I saved.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:50.59,0:21:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can only see them when \NI've had some of that sake,{yeah, i don't mind putting "the mushi" instead of "them" in 287, but i think it's clear enough. :)}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:52.78,0:21:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but whenever I do see them—\Nso vibrant and alive—{"when i  see those vibrant and alive beings" so you know exactly what he's  talking about. but i guess letting the visuals do the talking isn't a  bad compromise}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:57.19,0:22:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they help give me the strength to keep going.
